@bolkedebruin , we have a Hive statistic collection framework (named Stat Daemon, named after Matt :) built on Hive using Presto that monitors the metastore and scans every partition in Hive once (using Presto) and collecting all sort of metadata about each column and at the table level. The stats to collect are defined based on rule configuration based on on field naming conventions and data types that you can define yourself.  Say a STRING will collect a APPROX_COUNT_DISTINCT and a SUM(LENGTH(s)), and numerical values get SUM/MIN/MAX/STDDEV/... and so on. You can also define custom expressions like SUM(CASE WHEN, ...) and such.

We use the stats for data quality purposes and anomaly detection. 

We'd be happy to share, though it may not be in a 100% perfect sharable, documented state. I wonder how many folks are interested in stack-specific, higher level constructs built on top of Airflow. BTW if you use hive have you checked out the Hive Metastore Browser Airflow plugin that ships with Airflow?
